<br>
A: Here’s the answer, straight from the desk of the spell designer: <br>
<br>
&quot;Spells have a factor of (spell level / 2) added to their chance to hit. (Spell level defined as the level the spell is awarded, chance to hit defined as the chance of avoiding the &quot;Your target resists the spell!&quot; message.) Subtracted from the modified to-hit chance is the target's (level / 2). So a L50 caster casting a L30 spell at a L50 monster or player, they have a base chance of 85% to hit, plus 15%, minus 25% for a net chance to hit of 75%. If the chance to hit goes over 100% damage or duration is increased, and if it goes below 55%, you still have a 55% chance to hit but your damage or duration is penalized. If the chance to hit goes below 0, you cannot hit at all. Once the spell hits, damage and duration are further modified by resistances. <br>
<br>
&quot;In general, RvR is between opponents within 1 quanta of each other (in the frontiers for example, L45-50), and the spells cast are L40+. This results in a 2.5-5% modifier, which is somewhat lost in the noise of the bonuses from Int/Acuity, realm abilities, and modifiers from resistances. For characters using spells around L30, they will see a more significant reduction however, and this factor is part of it.&quot; <br>
<br>
Ever wondered why you cast all 4 of your shouts in a row and all 4 resisted on the same level 50 enemy? DD shouts are so weak its not even worth wasting the power and end to get a resist message. I don't know about you guys but I'm seriously looking for another class to play as my main which has use besides speedbot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/03 10:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wow</span><hr size=1> All I have to say is wow. This is a majorly retarded design decision. Wow.<br>
<br>
It always amaze me when I see that some pen and papers game systems (d20, d100, d6, whatever ...), after 10+ or 20+ years of release for some or them, countless changes and revamps, billions of gaming books and scores of versions, with a player base and design community that has open and transparent access to each single game rule, still strive to achieve some amount of balance, realism and fairness.<br>
<br>
Then, you have the MMORPGs, which, instead or using some existing system with a licence, create from scratch game mechanics (and generally, the authors are informaticians, not professionnal game designers).<br>
<br>
No wonder that every time one looks, every time some insight about game rules are released, we find some can of worms that can explains the zillions of game balance issues and problems we are all suffering from (thus, spawning even more stupid, patches, fixes, and other nerfs that break things more than they correct them).<br>
<br>
Wow, but then, again, I can't imagine someone came up with such a stupid system.<br>
<br>
What it means is that the level, the specialisation skill (or : &quot;how to make battlesong skill useful&quot;), the acuity score of the caster, not only are not the only factors that determinates if the spell is resisted or not, but the primary factor is (gasp) the way the spell list has been designed by Mythic from the start<br>
.<br>
It means, I am taking an example at random, that with equally maxed casting skill, level and acuity ability, a class that has its &quot;last&quot; damage or mez spell in a given spell line at skill 43 will always, always be more resisted (granted, by a moderate amount, but still), than a class whose  &quot;last&quot; spell is at skill 46. <br>
There is nothing you can do against it. Even going 50 skill + every realm rank and skill item bonus won't change it. Just because the spell lists between different classes have been created without rhyme or reason.<br>
<br>
Retarded.<br>
<br>
As for the skald, well, I wouldn't say we are gimped. This is a system which potentially hurt more or less randomly a lot of classes. However, then again, the classes than have an unique DD shout with high damage, low cost and low timer seem more advantaged than us, with our costly, long recycle &quot;secondary shout&quot; that has a hefty penalty just because it stops at level 34 (and even our &quot;primary&quot; shout caps somewhat low compared to other similar classes). Sigh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/03 1:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow</span><hr size=1> It is stupid...but don't exaggerate. Our lowest shout has a 8% higher resist rate than a lvl 50 spell, and our higher shout a 3% higher resist rate. Considering that the average resist rate on spells in the game is not going to be lvl 50 spells, the above numbers are the worst case scenario. More likely our lower shout is 6% higher resist than average and our higher shout is 1% higher resist than average. <br>
<br>
So when you get resisted 2 or 3 or 4 times in a row it's not cause BS shouts are gimped. It's just bad luck, like other casters have sometimes. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maximumstorage>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/03 11:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow</span><hr size=1> BTW did you notice the part where they say that dmg/duration is effected also not just resist rate?<br>
